description.p:
According to an aspect of the present invention, there is provided a wireless communication device, comprising:
circuitry configured to receive a request to send a data package to a target over a group communication channel;
circuitry configured to determine that at least one group communication channel is not established with a group communication server;
circuitry configured to selectively store the data package in a queue; circuitry configured to determine that a group communication channel has been established with at least the group communication server; and
circuitry configured to send all queued data packages to at least the group communication server via the established group communication channel.

According to an aspect of the present invention, there is provided a method, comprising:
receiving, at a wireless communication device, a request to send a data package to a target over a group communication channel;
determining if a group communication channel is open at the wireless communication device;
upon the determination that a group communication channel is not open at the wireless communication device, determining that the size of the data package is less than a predetermined size and storing the data package in a queue; and
upon a group communication channel being open, sending, from the wireless communication device, all stored data packages in the queue.

According to an aspect of the present invention, there is provided a wireless communication device, comprising:
means for receiving a request to send a data package to a target over a group communication channel;
means for determining that at least one group communication channel is not established with a group communication server;
means for selectively storing the data package in a queue;
means for determining that a group communication channel has been established with at least the group communication server; and
means for sending all queued data packages to at least the group communication server via the established group communication channel.

According to an aspect of the present invention, there is provided a computer system, comprising:
circuitry configured to receive a data package to from an originating wireless communication device over a group communication channel, the data package intended to be sent to one or more target group members of a communication group;
circuitry configured to determine that at least one target group member of the communication group does not have a group communication channel established thereto;
circuitry configured to selectively store the data package in a queue;
circuitry configured to determine that a group communication channel has been established with the at least one target group member; and
circuitry configured to send all queued data packages to the at least one target group member via the established group communication channel.

According to an aspect of the present invention, there is provided a method, comprising:
receiving over a group communication channel, at a at a group communication server, a data package sent from an originating wireless communication device to at least one target wireless communication device of a communication group; determining if a group communication channel is open for a target wireless communication device;
upon the determination that a group communication channel is not open for a target wireless communication device, determining that the size of the data package is less than a predetermined size;
storing the data package in a queue; and
upon a group communication channel being open to the target wireless communication device, sending all stored data packages in the queue for that wireless communication device.

According to an aspect of the present invention, there is provided a computer-readable product, comprising:
a computer-readable medium, comprising:
at least one set of instruction to receive over a group communication channel, at a at a group communication server, a data package sent from an originating wireless communication device to at least one target wireless communication device of a communication group; at least one set of instruction to determine if a group communication channel is open for a target wireless communication device;
at least one set of instruction to, upon the determination that a group communication channel is not open for a target wireless communication device, determine that the size of the data package is less than a predetermined size;
at least one set of instruction to store the data package in a queue; and
at least one set of instruction to, upon a group communication channel being open to the target wireless communication device, send all stored data packages in the queue for that wireless communication device.

claim.claim-text:
A method for use in a wireless communications device, comprising:
receiving a request to send a non-voice data package to a target over a group communication channel;
determining whether at least one push-to-talk communication channel is established with a group communication server;
wherein if a push-to-talk communication channel is not established, selectively storing the data package in a queue; and
subsequent to storing the data package in the queue, determining that a push-to-talk communication channel has been established with the target; and
in response to the determination, sending all queued data packages to at least the group communication server via the established push-to-talk communication channel;
wherein the data package is selectively stored in the queue prior to sending a request to set up a push-to-talk communication channel with the group communication server.

A wireless communications device comprising:
means for receiving a request to send a non-voice data package to a target over a group communication channel;
means for determining whether at least one push-to-talk communication channel is established with a group communication server;
means for selectively storing the data package in a queue in response to a determination that a push-to-talk communication channel is not established; and
means for determining, subsequent to storing the data package in the queue, that a push-to-talk communication channel has been established with the target; and
means for sending all queued data packages to at least the group communication server via the established push-to-talk communication channel in response to the determination;
wherein the means for selectively storing stores the data package in the queue prior to sending a request to set up a push-to-talk communication channel with the group communication server.
